        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2012-12-05 22:27:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/a25ace26-3f27-11e2-856e-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a3405bcb916b05a2d4b1155b91231c49c44d0453",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-12-05 23:49:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nIn large scale IR testing, I found that the notify thread can't be scheduled in time after the IR lock is actually granted because there are so many IR lock enqueue request from clients. So I have to work out a patch to cancel on completion, and this way solved the problem perfectly.\n\nI'd like to keep it current way if it doesn't break anything.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
